		<td><b>Re: How to fix a NES that won't turn on ?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">socram8888 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I have not seen ever a NES with dead capacitors, so don't replace any yet.</div><br />I would also second replacing the 7805 first but I would also take a look at the big filter cap. I've seen them go bad based on some of the NESes that I've worked on; I even had one that was bulging at the top so it was obviously bad. Sometimes the caps inside the RF/AV box go bad which happened with another NES I had.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
